4. The policy data model and relationships to other entities (vehicles, locations, coverages) need to be solidified upfront.

5. Once the policy foundation is in place, it will be easier to integrate the Claims and Payments modules in a cohesive way.

So in summary, my recommendation is to focus the initial implementation effort on the Policy Management endpoints, then expand to Claims and Payments as the next priorities. This aligns with the core requirements and will provide the most foundational capabilities to build upon.
